      • core.VNode

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Directory
extends VNode
    A representation of a directory in the virtual file system. A Directory object contains a list of files/directories.

      • Directory

        Directory(java.lang.String name)
        Creates a directory. This constructor is package private becase a directory cannot exist on its own. It must be created through a virtual file system.
        Parameters:
        name - name of the directory

        adds a VNode to the directory content list. It modifies the size of all parents of the directory.
        Parameters:
        child - VNode to add as child in the tree structure
        Throws:
        exceptions.NameAlreadyExistsException - if the directory already contains a VNode with the same name in its content list
        exceptions.NoFreeSpaceLeftException - if the directory's virtual disk doesn't have enough free space to add this new VNode
